div.p:
IN the Reign of King Edward the Fourth the Pope granted to the Prior of Saint Johns to have Sanctuary within his Priory;
                     1 H. 7. fol. 20.
                   and this was pleaded and claimed by the Prior: But it was reſolved by the Judges, that the Pope had no power to grant any Sanctuary within this Realm, and therefore by judgement of the Law the ſame was diſallowed.
